My contributions included helping develop the project concept, assisting with the Arduino code, and preparing the presentation
used during the demonstration.

Although having many ideas and most discarded due to unfeasibility we ended up with the ASEC one since my
project partner said it was the one most worth pursuing due to it's practicality and simplicity.
Personally for me the idea was influenced by my problem of losing focus while studying due to distractions such as social 
media (in my case instagram reels), noise, and interruptions. This led to the concept of building a device that could 
monitor environmental conditions and provide feedback to help maintain concentration during study sessions.

The concept was discussed and refined with my project partner Michael, and the final design focused on using sensors 
connected to an Arduino to monitor the study environment.

Technical Contributions

- Assisting with the Arduino code (only the day that my Project partner didn't show up to class, didn't touch the code since)
