The project provided practical experience with Arduino programming and sensor integration. 
It involved learning how environmental data can be collected from sensors and processed into useful information.
It also provided experience with reading data from multiple sensors, processing sensor inputs to generate a focus score,
displaying system information on an OLED display and using external tools to assist with coding and debugging.

Reflection

The project taught me that arduino devices can be used to tackle real-world problems such as distractions and lack of focus
by keeping environmental factors such as noise, lighting, and interruptions in control.
If the project were developed further, additional features could include mobile app connectivity, cloud data storage, and 
long-term tracking of study conditions, allowing users to better understand and improve their study habits over time.
To finish it off I think that I should probably limit my usage of Artifical Intelligence next time as I heavily depended on
